cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper is concerned with automata and their properties.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses computational complexity and algorithms for equivalence and minimisation.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper uses polynomial identity testing and the Isolation Lemma.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of the problems considered.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is less likely but still possible as the paper considers probabilistic automata with rewards, which are similar to Markov Decision Processes used in AI.
